  "texts": [
    "formance by adding multiple self-attention modules, which is unsustainable due to the disproportionate increase in parameters relative to performance gains (Yao et al. 2024).",
    "Instead, SPECAT employs Cumulative-Attention-Blocks (CABs) within an efficient hierarchical framework, effectively capturing non-local spatial and spectral details in hyperspectral images.",
    "These blocks consist of Hierarchical Spatial Attention (HSA), Mask Attention (MA), and Global Spectral Attention blocks, leveraging spectral correlations to enhance image reconstruction.",
    "Notably, CABs facilitate the extraction of spatial information across spectral bands by processing each local spatial feature map as a token and applying selfattention within the spatial domain.",
    "Furthermore, SPECAT utilizes a novel Dual-domain Loss Function (DLF), specifically formulated to incorporate the physical model of spectral reconstruction, ensuring enhanced training efficacy and model robustness."
  ]
}